Nice, clear instructions!  I've been using VLC forever, but I still don´t know half the tricks it can do.

One task you might be able to help me with pls?  
I have a lot of amateur videos shot on phones, where they've rotated the phone over and over, but don't have "auto-rotate" enabled.  I need a user-friendly program that will let me 
1. view the entire clip; 
2. let me select a portion from [time] to [time] and rotate it by 90, 180 or 270º; 
3. apply to that selection; 
4. repeat for as many sections as are skewed; 
5. Save to a new file

Do you know anything that can do this without me needing a Doctorate in Rocket Surgery to make it work?
Even VLC has SO many steps to correct a shonky video I can never get it right.
